Mesh Analysis

General Approach
Depending on the direction of current (Current flows from higher to lower potential), polarities are assigned to elements as follows:

For \[
\begin{array}
a_1 I_1 + b_1 I_2 = c_1
a_1 I_1+ b_2 I_2 = c_2
\]
\[
\begin{align*}
I_1 = \frac{
    \begin{matrix}
        c_1 & b_1
        c_2 & b_2
    \end{matrix}
    }{
    \begin{matrix}
        a_1 & b_1
        a_2 & b_2
    \end{matrix}
    } \\
I_2 = \frac{
    \begin{matrix}
        a_1 & c_1
        a_2 & c_2
    \end{matrix}
    }{
    \begin{matrix}
        a_1 & b_1
        a_2 & b_2
    \end{matrix}
    }
\end{align*}
\]

Here, as per KVL:
\[\begin{align*}
    E_1 - I_1 Z_1 - (I_1 - I_2) Z_2 = 0 \\
    E_1 - I_1 Z_1 - I_1 Z_2 + I_2 Z_2 = 0 \\
    E_1 - I_1 (Z_1 + Z_2) + I_2 Z_2 = 0 \\
    \boxed{- I_1 (Z_1 + Z_2) + I_2 Z_2 = -E_1} \\
    -(I_2 - I_1) Z_2 - I_2 Z_3 - E_2 = 0 \\
    -I_2 Z_2 + I_1 Z_2 - I_2 Z_3 - E_2 = 0 \\
    -I_2 (Z_2 + Z_3) + I_1 Z_2 = E_2 \\
\end{align*}\]
Now you have your equations, assign theme


Format Approach
For loop 1:
$ I_1 ( Z_x ) - I_2 ( Z_x ) = E_x $
For loop 2:
$ - I_1 ( Z_x ) + I_2 ( Z_x ) = E_x $
